verbose_text: The CCR6 receptor (CC chemokine receptor type 6) is the only known receptor for CCL20 and is expressed in the lymphatic system and also outside of it, including the spleen, lymph nodes, appendix, thymus, small intestine, pancreas, and peripheral blood leukocytes - T and B lymphocytes and dendritic cells [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR].
